When BUILTIN=OFF we link against the conda pythia6 package via the bundled
FindPythia6.cmake, which creates a Pythia6::Pythia6 IMPORTED target locally.
That target is NOT part of the install(EXPORT) set, so the generated
ROOTEGPythia6Targets.cmake ends up with INTERFACE_LINK_LIBRARIES that
references a target the consumer's CMake scope doesn't know about — e.g.
FairShip's `find_package(ROOTEGPythia6 REQUIRED)` then dies with:

    The link interface of target "ROOT::EGPythia6" contains:
        Pythia6::Pythia6
      but the target was not found.

Demote the link to PRIVATE so libEGPythia6.so still gets the DT_NEEDED for
libPythia6.so at link time, without leaking the unresolvable target name
into the exported interface.

TODO: open upstream PR against luketpickering/ROOTEGPythia6 so we can
drop this patch.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -59,7 +59,7 @@

 add_library(ROOT::EGPythia6 ALIAS EGPythia6)

-target_link_libraries(EGPythia6 PUBLIC ROOT::EG Pythia6::Pythia6)
+target_link_libraries(EGPythia6 PUBLIC ROOT::EG PRIVATE Pythia6::Pythia6)
 target_include_directories(EGPythia6 PUBLIC 
   $<BUILD_INTERFACE:${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/inc>
   $<INSTALL_INTERFACE:include>)
